5 components that will be in scope for integration testing in the website:
1)User Authentication System: This component manages user authentication 
and authorization, including user login, registration, and session management.
2)Product Catalog and Inventory Management: This component handles the management 
of products available for sale, including adding, updating, 
and removing products from the catalog, as well as managing inventory levels.
3)Shopping Cart and Order Processing: This component allows users to add 
products to their shopping cart, update quantities, and proceed to checkout. It also manages 
the processing of orders, including order validation, payment processing, and order fulfillment.
4)Payment Gateway Integration: This component integrates with third-party payment gateways to facilitate
secureonline payments. It handles payment authorization, transaction processing, and response handling.
5)User Reviews and Ratings: This component enables users to leave reviews and ratings for products they 
have purchased.It manages the storage and retrieval of user reviews, as well as the display of ratings on product pages
